SIMPLE: netting
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Netting
<hw>Net"ting</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[From <er>Net</er>,
<pos>n.</pos>]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The act or process of making nets
or network, or of forming meshes, as for fancywork, fishing nets,
etc.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A piece of network; any fabric, made of cords,
threads, wires, or the like, crossing one another with open spaces
between.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Naut.)</fld> <def>A network of ropes used for
various purposes, as for holding the hammocks when not in use, also for
stowing sails, and for hoisting from the gunwale to the rigging to
hinder an enemy from boarding.</def> <rj><au>Totten.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Netting needle</b></col>, <cd>a kind of slender shuttle
used in netting. See <er>Needle</er>, <pos>n.</pos>, 3.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Netting</ent>⟦br⟧

